            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel and chop the <strong>brown onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> into wedges</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped onion</strong> to the pan with 1 tsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>flour </strong>and the<strong> dried thyme</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and add 200ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[375ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> with the <strong>tomato paste</strong>,<strong> beef stock mix</strong>,<strong> soy sauce</strong>, <strong>bay leaf<span class=\"text-danger\">[ves]</span> </strong>and<strong> red wine paste</strong></p><p>Bring to the boil over a high heat – this is your<strong> pie mix</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
